  "time_ut": 1658752723,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dbb\u0dcf\u0da2\u0dd2\u0dad\u0d9c\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca \u0d85\u0da7\u0dda \u0db1\u0da9\u0dd4\u0dc0 \u0d89\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dcf \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d9a\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dd3",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Rajitha's eight-ship case is withdrawn",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Criminal Investigation Department, Colombo Additional Magistrate Mr. Keminda Perera announced today (25) that the case regarding the bringing of 08 ships to Sri Lanka and the leasing of Modara fishing port during the tenure of MP Rajitha Senaratne as the Minister of Fisheries will be withdrawn.",
        "The Criminal Investigation Department informed the court that since the Bribery Commission has filed a case against Parliamentarian Mr. Rajitha Senaratne under the charge of 'corruption' in relation to this incident, the case pending in this court will be withdrawn.",
        "Accordingly, the Magistrate allowed the CID to withdraw the case.",
        "These facts were presented today (25) when the Magistrate's inquiry related to the incident was called.",
        "State Minister Sanath Nishantha Perera had submitted a complaint to the Criminal Investigation Department regarding this incident stating that these 08 ships had been brought to Sri Lanka under an agreement with a Chinese company in the name of Don Lalith Anuradha Seneviratne, who worked as a coordination secretary of former Fisheries Minister Rajitha Senaratne.",
        "Also, it has been reported to the court that the prosecution has asked the Criminal Investigation Department to start an investigation regarding the lease of Modara port to a foreign company mentioned in the complaint."
      ],
